6.0.0								>= 2.5.0		>= 1.8.11	
5.0.0 to 5.2.x			>= 2.2.2		>= 1.8.11	
4.2.x								>= 1.9.3		2.2						>= 1.8.11	
4.1.x to 4.2.0			>= 1.9.3		2.1						>= 1.8.11	
4.0.5 to 4.1.0.rc2	>= 1.9.3									>= 1.8.11	
4.0.0 to 4.0.x			>= 1.8.7									>= 1.8.11	
3.2.22 to 3.2.22.5	1.8.7				2.2						>= 1.3.6	
3.2.13 to 3.2.22.4	1.8.7				2.0						>= 1.3.6	
0.8.0 to 3.2.13.rc2	1.8.7											>= 1.3.6	


----------------------

https://guides.rubyonrails.org/upgrading_ruby_on_rails.html#ruby-versions


Rails 6 requires Ruby 2.5.0 or newer.
Rails 5 requires Ruby 2.2.2 or newer.
Rails 4 prefers Ruby 2.0 and requires 1.9.3 or newer.
Rails 3.2.x is the last branch to support Ruby 1.8.7.
Rails 3 and above require Ruby 1.8.7 or higher. Support for all of the previous Ruby versions has been dropped officially. You should upgrade as early as possible.



